{'html': '<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">\r<html>\r<head>\r<title>e s c a p e</title>\r<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">\r<meta name="description" content="esc-design, interaction design for dynamic interactive environments, 7c Sunderland Terrace, London W2 5PA, UK">\r<meta name="keywords" content=" escape design, esc design, architecture, design, interaction, dynamic interactive environments, performance, performativity, Mixed Reality, Augmented Reality, games, playful interaction, Mette Ramsgard Thomsen, Jesper Mortensen, bartlett, ucl, university of brighton, brighton, London">\r<script language="JavaScript" type="text/JavaScript">\r<!--\rfunction MM_reloadPage(init) {  //reloads the window if Nav4 resized\r  if (init==true) with (navigator) {if ((appName=="Netscape")&&(parseInt(appVersion)==4)) {\r    document.MM_pgW=innerWidth; document.MM_pgH=innerHeight; onresize=MM_reloadPage; }}\r  else if (innerWidth!=document.MM_pgW || innerHeight!=document.MM_pgH) location.reload();\r}\rMM_reloadPage(true);\r\rfunction MM_openBrWindow(theURL,winName,features) { //v2.0\r  window.open(theURL,winName,features);\r}\r//-->\r</script>\r<link href="text.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">\r</head>\r\r<body bgcolor="999999" background="images/backgroundimage.jpg" text="#FFFFFF">\r<div id="Layer1" style="position:absolute; left:0px; top:188px; width:1300px; height:44px; z-index:1"><img src="images/titlebar.gif" width="1300" height="44" border="0" usemap="#Map"> \r  <map name="Map">\r    <area shape="rect" coords="430,15,493,37" href="profile.html">\r    <area shape="rect" coords="545,16,625,36" href="projects.html">\r    <area shape="rect" coords="671,17,746,36" href="people.html">\r    <area shape="rect" coords="786,16,880,38" href="contacts.html">\r    <area shape="rect" coords="30,1,272,38" href="index.html">\r  </map>\r</div>\r<div id="Layer2" style="position:absolute; left:430px; top:270; width:450; height:850; z-index:2"> \r  <h1>I see what you hear</h1>\r  <p><em>I see what you hear</em> is a dynamic interactive environment for intuitive \r    interaction. The installation merges the users&#8217; sound output [talking, \r    singing and making noises] with the dynamic production of a 3 dimensional \r    space generated as clouds of matter that the user &#8216;blows&#8217; into \r    being. Swarms of insects, leaves, fish, circles, numbers, create a spatial \r    density around the presence and action of the user. Like a snowstorm, the \r    space is a condition rather than a limitation, defined by the quality and \r    deliberations of interaction. The individual textures are mapped onto the \r    pitch level creating bands of matter within the installation space. The users&#8217; \r    sound production scaling across these bands as well as the gravity of particle \r    stream mixes the textures together into worlds of their own. </p>\r  <p><img src="images/iswyh1.jpg" width="450" height="112"></p>\r  <p>As the users learn to control the parameters of interaction they learn to \r    generate spaces of singular objects or mix together different objects of choice. \r    The environment is presented stereoscopically allowing the user to be sited \r    within the spatial density.</p>\r  <p><img src="images/iswyh2.jpg" width="450" height="112"></p>\r  <p>In <em>I see what you hear</em> the digital is instantiated in the present, \r    coming into being through the moment of interaction. When the user is still, \r    or quiet, the presence of the digital dissolves, returning the user to the \r    normative containing environment. The digital becomes an enacted dimension, \r    a durational space taking place across the temporal extensions of experience. \r  </p>\r  <p><em>I see what you hear </em>was exhibited at <em>Embodied Interfaces</em> \r    at the Grand Parade Gallery, University of Brighton, Dec 2002.</p>\r  <p><a href="iswyh.html" onClick="MM_openBrWindow(\'iswyh_mov_high.html\',\'video\',\'width=330,height=265\')">video \r    high res (14 mb)</a><br>\r    <a href="iswyh.html" onClick="MM_openBrWindow(\'iswyh_mov_low.html\',\'video\',\'width=330,height=265\')">video \r    low res (3.4 mb)</a> </p>\r  </div>\r</body>\r</html>\r',
